      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(claude): add claude-bridge app-server harness extension",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nInspiration: https://openclaw.ai/blog/openai-models-in-openclaw-done-right; achieve parity for Claude\r\n\r\nOpenClaw currently has no first-class harness for Anthropic models. Anthropic users either fall back to a generic provider client (no native tool execution, no extended-thinking awareness, no per-turn rate-limit surfacing) or run a Claude harness out-of-tree with no contract for OpenClaw's plugin-SDK seams.\r\n\r\nThe codex harness already ships in-tree with the same shape we want — `extensions/codex/src/app-server/` is a codex-app-server JSON-RPC client over stdio. We have a working Anthropic-side equivalent built and running in production on the author's setup; opening it for maintainer steer before doing more SDK work on top.\r\n\r\n**What is the intended outcome?**\r\n\r\n- Bundled extension `@openclaw/claude` registers `claude-bridge` as a harness option in the model picker.\r\n- At turn-start, the extension spawns an `openclaw-claude-bridge` subprocess and speaks the codex-shaped JSON-RPC protocol over stdio. The server (currently published as `@zeroaltitude/openclaw-claude-bridge` — fork-preview path; would migrate to `@openclaw/openclaw-claude-bridge` if the maintainers republish it) handles Anthropic API I/O, rate-limit surfacing, image-payload sanitization, and plugin-thread-config persistence.\r\n- Bridge-side handles event projection into OpenClaw's notification/accumulator surface, transcript mirroring with idempotency keys, dynamic-tool aggregate output cap, vision-tools de-duplication, and `/claude` slash commands.\r\n- See `extensions/claude/README.md` for the full feature map.\r\n\r\n**What is intentionally out of scope?**\r\n\r\n- Republishing the server under `@openclaw/openclaw-claude-bridge` — needs maintainer decision; the `@zeroaltitude` scope dependency is the current placeholder.\r\n- Migrating to OpenClaw's standard plugin-SDK provider hooks beyond what `extensions/codex/` already uses. The bridge follows codex's pattern verbatim where applicable.\r\n- Anything outside the harness bridge surface.\r\n\r\n**What does success look like?** Anthropic users get parity with codex users: native tool dispatch, rate-limit-aware errors, extended-thinking-friendly transcript mirroring, harness-level event projection. No regressions to existing harnesses.\r\n\r\n**What should reviewers focus on?**\r\n\r\n1. **Scope concern — am I taking too much core?** The branch touches `src/plugins/command-registration.ts`, `src/plugins/current-plugin-metadata-snapshot.ts`, `src/plugins/agent-tool-result-middleware-types.ts`, `src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-native-slash-fast-path.ts`, `src/agents/model-runtime-aliases.ts`, and `src/agents/tools/image-tool.ts`. Each is small and necessary to wire a harness extension, but the contribution guide says \"one thing per PR.\" Happy to split into prep PRs first if maintainers prefer.\r\n2. **External-plugin vs. bundled-extension** — Per CONTRIBUTING.md \"most features should be third-party plugins.\" Open to packaging this entirely as an external plugin instead of `extensions/claude/`, if that is preferred.\r\n3. **Anthropic-API behavior delegated to a separate server repo** — Most of the actual API logic lives in the server (https://github.com/zeroaltitude/openclaw-plugins/tree/main/openclaw-claude/server). Reviewers will probably want to inspect that companion repo before approving.\r\n4. **`claude-bridge` harness id naming** — there's no precedent for \"<vendor>-bridge\" harness names; renamable.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n\r\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Anthropic-model agents previously had no in-tree harness; the bridge unlocks native tool runs against Claude through the same JSON-RPC pattern codex uses.\r\n- **Real environment tested:** Author's openclaw gateway running on Linux (WSL2 / Ubuntu), Node 22.x. Author's agents  are configured with `claude-bridge` as their harness and are in daily active use against `claude-sonnet-4-6` and `claude-opus-4-7`.\r\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\r\n  1. `pnpm install && pnpm build`\r\n  2. `openclaw gateway restart --deep`\r\n  3. Send a Slack DM to one of the claude-bridge agents\r\n  4. Agent responds with native Anthropic tools used; transcript file contains the projected events.\r\n  5. `/claude status` in the same thread prints shared-client liveness.\r\n- **Evidence after fix:** Daily-driver production use (multiple Slack threads/turns per day) over the past ~2 weeks on the author's setup. Tank (a codex-harness agent) and Tabitha (claude-bridge) work side-by-side on the same gateway. Transcript files at `~/.openclaw/agents/<id>/transcripts/` show the projected event stream. No fresh standalone capture for this PR; proof is the ongoing production usage.\r\n- **Observed result after fix:** Anthropic turns complete normally; tool calls fire; rate-limit messages are user-actionable; resume across restart works via the `.claude-binding.json` sidecar.\r\n- **What was not tested:**\r\n  - Windows/macOS gateway hosts (only Linux/WSL2 verified).\r\n  - Bun runtime (Node 22 only).\r\n  - Anthropic enterprise/Bedrock/Vertex API surfaces (only public Anthropic API).\r\n  - Concurrent multi-account scenarios beyond 3 agents.\r\n- **Proof limitations or environment constraints:** Author runs a single-host gateway. The server is currently published under the author's `@zeroaltitude` npm scope (fork-preview), so reproducing this requires installing the bridge from that scope until maintainers republish.\r\n- **Before evidence:** N/A — no prior in-tree harness for Anthropic to compare against.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n\r\n- `pnpm build` ✓ (local)\r\n- `pnpm test extensions/claude` ✓ (local — extension unit tests, including event projector, dynamic-tools middleware port, thread fork policy envelope, transcript mirror dedupe)\r\n- `pnpm test:extensions` not run since last rebase — recommend Testbox/Crabbox run before non-draft review.\r\n- No `CHANGELOG.md` edit per contributor rule; maintainer to add on land.\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n\r\n- **Did user-visible behavior change?** Yes — new `claude-bridge` harness appears in model picker; new `/claude` slash command surface.\r\n- **Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** Yes — new plugin `configSchema` (see `extensions/claude/openclaw.plugin.json`). Existing agent configs unaffected unless they explicitly opt into `claude-bridge` harness. Doctor contract added (`extensions/claude/doctor-contract-api.ts`).\r\n- **Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** Yes (intentional). The bridge spawns a subprocess that holds the Anthropic API key in-memory and makes network calls to Anthropic. Subprocess lifecycle is owned by the harness, not user shell. The plugin SDK enabler changes (e.g. `command-registration.ts`) are additive and follow existing codex-extension precedent.\r\n- **Highest-risk area:** Server-bridge stdio lifecycle and the few SDK enabler edits in `src/plugins/**`. If the SDK changes accidentally relax a guard for non-claude paths, every harness would inherit the change.\r\n- **How is that risk mitigated?** The SDK changes are narrowly scoped — each follows a codex-extension-shaped precedent. Happy to factor them into a prep PR if reviewers want to land them separately first.\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\n\r\n- **Next action:** Maintainer steer on scope: (a) accept as bundled extension as-is, (b) split SDK enablers into a prep PR first, or (c) request packaging as an external plugin.\r\n- **Still waiting on:** Maintainer decision on the above. CI run on this push.\r\n- **Bot/reviewer comments addressed:** None yet — opening draft.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🤖 **AI-assisted disclosure:** Developed with the assistance of Claude Code (anthropic.com/claude-code). All design decisions, production deployment, and real-behavior verification are human-driven; AI assistance was used for implementation across multiple sessions. Session transcripts available on request.\r\n",
